document_notes.text:
This update for libqt5-qtbase fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2023-45935: Fixed NULL pointer dereference in QXcbConnection::initializeAllAtoms() due to anomalous behavior from the X server (bsc#1222120)
- CVE-2024-39936: Fixed information leakage due to process HTTP2 communication before encrypted() can be responded to (bsc#1227426)

notes.text: ** DISPUTED ** Qt 6 through 6.6 was discovered to contain a NULL pointer dereference via the function QXcbConnection::initializeAllAtoms(). NOTE: this is disputed because it is not expected that an X application should continue to run when there is arbitrary anomalous behavior from the X server.

notes.text: An issue was discovered in HTTP2 in Qt before 5.15.18, 6.x before 6.2.13, 6.3.x through 6.5.x before 6.5.7, and 6.6.x through 6.7.x before 6.7.3. Code to make security-relevant decisions about an established connection may execute too early, because the encrypted() signal has not yet been emitted and processed..
